{"name": "the-glam", "metadata": {"name": "the-glam", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["glycowork", "pyteomics"], "summary": "The Glycopeptide Analysis Module", "upload_time": 1732537953}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "glam", "documentation": ["A (very) small package for generating\n[PGFinder](https://github.com/Mesnage-Org/pgfinder)-compatible glycopeptide\ndatabases.\n\nJust supply a FASTA file containing the protein(s) of interest,\nspecify the digestion parameters, a glycosylation motif, and a list of potential\nglycan compositions / structures.\n\n# INCLUDE A SHORT CODE EXAMPLE HERE!\nWe can include a markdown file that shows how to use the web interface /\nwhatever other documentation seems useful!\n```py\nprint(\"Test?\")\n```"], "functions": [{"name": "glam.generate_glycopeptides", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fasta", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "digestion", "type": {"name": "str | Pattern[str]", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "motif", "type": {"name": "str | Pattern[str]", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "glycans", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "missed_cleavages", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "min_length", "type": {"name": "int | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_length", "type": {"name": "int | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "semi_enzymatic", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Generates glycopeptides from an input FASTA and CSV file of glycans.\n\nParameters\n----------\nfasta : str,\n    FASTA text describing the protein sequence(s) to be digested. Note that this\n    function ***does not*** read from the filesystem \u2014 you'll need to first load\n    your FASTA file into a `str` using something like `pathlib.Path.read_text`.\nenzyme : str or Pattern[str],\n    The name of the enyzme used to digest the protein into peptides. A number of\n    enzymes are built-in (see `pyteomics.parser.expasy_rules` and\n    `pyteomics.parser.psims_rules`), but a custom (optionally pre-compiled)\n    regex describing the enzyme's cleavage site can also be supplied. For more\n    information, see `pyteomics`'s documentation.\nmotif : str or Pattern[str],\n    A regex describing the sequence motif for glycosylation. Only peptides\n    containing this motif will be used to generate the final list of glycopeptides.\n    See the `glam.GLYCOSYLATION_MOTIFS` dictionary for common motifs.\nglycans : str,\n\nmissed_cleavages : int, default: 0,\n    The maximum number of missed cleavages to allow during digestion\nmin_length : int or None, default: None,\n    The minimum length peptide to include in the digest output\nmax_length : int or None, default: None,\n    The maximum length peptide to include in the digest output\nsemi : bool, default: False,", "Functions ====================================================================", "FIXME: This docstring is still out of date / wrong!"]}], "variables": [{"name": "glam.DIGESTIONS", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "